    "Techniques such as model quantization, pruning, and the use of transformer-based neural networks on specialized hardware (e.g., TPUs) can help reduce computational overhead while maintaining accuracy.",
    "Additionally, there is a scarcity of standardized benchmarking datasets and protocols for odor classification.",
    "Most existing datasets are either proprietary or lack comprehensive metadata, such as information about environmental conditions or chemical concentrations.",
    "Developing open-source benchmarking datasets with a diverse range of molecular data and odor descriptors would facilitate reproducibility and accelerate progress in this field.",
    "For broader challenges such as subjective perception variability, AI interpretability, and multimodal integration, please refer to the consolidated discussion in Sect. 5.3, which addresses these shared challenges comprehensively."
